The '''''SIAM Journal on Applied Mathematics''''' is a [[peer review|peer-reviewed]] [[academic journal]] in [[applied mathematics]] published by the [[Society for Industrial and Applied Mathematics]] (SIAM), with Paul A. Martin as its editor-in-chief. It was founded in 1953 as SIAM's first journal,<ref>{{citation|url=https://www.siam.org/journals/siap.php|title=SIAM Journal on Applied Mathematics (SIAP)|publisher=[[Society for Industrial and Applied Mathematics]]|accessdate=2016-01-25}}.</ref> the ''Journal of the Society for Industrial and Applied Mathematics'', and was given its current name in 1966.<ref>{{citation|url=http://www.scholarly-societies.org/history/SIAMJApplMath.html|title=SIAM Journal on Applied Mathematics Continues Journal of the Society for Industrial and Applied Mathematics|work=History of Scholarly Societies|publisher=Scholarly Societies Project, University of Waterloo Library|accessdate=2016-01-25}}.</ref> In most years since 1999, it has been ranked by [[SCImago Journal Rank]] as a second-quartile journal in applied mathematics.<ref>{{citation|url=http://www.scimagojr.com/journalsearch.php?q=26404&tip=sid|title=SIAM Journal on Applied Mathematics|publisher=[[SCImago Journal Rank]]|accessdate=2016-01-25}}.</ref> Together with ''[[Communications on Pure and Applied Mathematics]]'' it has been called "one of the two greatest American entries in applied math".<ref>{{citation|title=Journals of the Century|first1=Jim|last1=Cole|first2=Tony|last2=Stankus|publisher=Routledge|year=2014|isbn=9781317720140|page=345|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=Pv7sAgAAQBAJ&pg=PA345}}.</ref>

