'''Workshop on Numerical Ranges and Numerical Radii (WONRA)''' is a biennial workshop series on [[numerical range]]s and numerical radii which began in 1992. ==About== Numerical ranges and numerical radii are useful in the study of matrix and operator theory. These topics have applications in many subjects in pure and applied mathematics, such as [[quadratic forms]], [[Banach spaces]], [[dilation theory]], [[control theory]], [[numerical analysis]], [[quantum information science]].<ref>{{cite book|last1=Bhatia|first1=R.|title=Matrix Analysis|date=1997|publisher=Springer-Verlag|isbn=0387948465|pages=349|url=https://www.springer.com/us/book/9780387948461}}</ref> <ref>{{cite book|last1=Bonsall|first1=F.|last2=Duncan|first2=J.|title=Numerical Ranges of Operators on Normed Spaces and of Elements of Normed Algebras|date=1971|publisher= Cambridge University Press|isbn=0521079888|pages=148}}</ref> <ref>{{cite book|last1=Bonsall|first1=F.|last2=Duncan|first2=J.|title=Numerical Ranges II, Vol. 2|date=1973|publisher= Cambridge University Press|isbn=0521202272|pages=179}}</ref> <ref>{{cite book|last1=Gustafson |first1=K.E.|last2=Rao|first2=D.K.M.|title=Numerical Range: The Field of Values of Linear Operators and Matrices|date=1997|publisher=Springer-Verlag|isbn=038794835X|pages=190|url=https://www.springer.com/gp/book/9780387948355}}</ref> <ref>{{cite book|last1=Istratescu|first1=B.|title=Introduction to Linear Operator Theory|date=1982|publisher=Marcel Dekker|isbn= 0824768965|pages=608}}</ref> <ref>{{cite book|last1=Halmos |first1=P.R.|title=A Hilbert Space Problem Book|date=1982|publisher=Springer-Verlag|isbn=0387906851|pages=373|url=https://link.springer.com/book/10.1007%2F978-1-4615-9976-0}}</ref> <ref>{{cite book|last1=Horn|first1=R.A.|last2=Johnson|first2=C.R.|title=Topics in Matrix Analysis|date=1991|publisher= Cambridge University Press|isbn=0521467136|pages=616}}</ref> ==History== In the early 1970s, numerical range workshops were organized by [[Frank Bonsall]] and John Duncan. More activities were started in early 1990s, including the biennial workshop series, which began in 1992, and special issues devoted to this workshop were published.<ref>{{cite journal|last1=Ando|first1=T.|last2=Li|first2=C.K.|last3=(special editors)|title=Special issue devoted to WONRA|journal=Linear and Multilinear Algebra|date=1994|volume=37|issue=1-3}}</ref> <ref>{{cite journal|last1=Ando|first1=T.|last2=Li|first2=C.K.|last3=(special editors)|title=Special issue devoted to WONRA|journal=Linear and Multilinear Algebra|date=1998|volume=43|issue=4}}</ref> <ref>{{cite journal|last1=Li|first1=C.K.|last2=Tam|first2=T.Y.|last3=(special editors)|title=Special issue devoted to WONRA|journal=Linear and Multilinear Algebra|date=2006|volume=52|issue=3-4}}</ref> <ref>{{cite journal|last1=Li|first1=C.K.|last2=Tam|first2=T.Y.|last3=(special editors)|title=Special issue devoted to WONRA|journal=Linear and Multilinear Algebra|date=2009|volume=57|issue=5}}</ref>
